<h2 id="how-it-works">How Enclomiphene Works (Mechanism of Action)</h2>

<p>Enclomiphene works by selectively blocking estrogen receptors in the hypothalamus and pituitary gland:</p>

<ol style="margin: 24px 0;">
  <li><strong>Blocks estrogen receptors</strong> ‚Üí Brain thinks estrogen is low</li>
  <li><strong>Pituitary releases more LH and FSH</strong> ‚Üí Signal to produce testosterone</li>
  <li><strong>Testes produce 2-2.5x more testosterone</strong> ‚Üí Levels rise naturally</li>
  <li><strong>Sperm production continues</strong> ‚Üí Fertility maintained</li>
</ol>

